			<tr><td colspan="2">
				<div class="postbody">
				The transition to the new plan would require borrowing trillions of dollars. But then, if you signed up for the piratized accounts, you'd be borrowing from the Feds, and would have to pay back the loan (with interest) when you rolled the amount into an annuity at age 67.
<br />

<br />
Transition costs are estimated at $20 Trillion over 3 decades. That is several times the national debt. To fund it without debt would involve doubling federal income taxes for the next 30 years.
<br />

<br />
It is this transition that caused every country that attempted to privatize their equivalent to SocSec to go heavily into debt. 
<br />

<br />
The trustees of SocSec produce 3 estimates of the future: an optimistic projection, a pessimistic projection and one in-between. The estimates/projections are based upon things like growth of the economy, population growth and a whole bunch of other things. The projection claiming that SocSec will go tits up in 2020 (or there abouts) is based off the pessimistic forecast. The projection claiming piratized accounts will make you all rich is based off the optimistic forecast. Of course, they don't want you to know that under the optimistic forecast, there will not be any funding problems with SocSec before 2150. But the bush cronies are betting that you cannot do math and that slogans are more potent than truth. The projections claiming you'll do better under piratized accounts also assume things like stock prices will go up about twice as much as they have done in the last 50 years.
<br />

<br />
If you want a personal retirement account, set up an IRA and a 401k (if your company offers one). Social Security wasn't meant to replace them, but to be a safety net if your pensions and personal savings went bust.<br />
				<span class="gensmall"></span><br />
				</div>
